<h1>Listing Equipment Black Outs</h1>
<br>
If a user tries to create a reservation for any of the equipment models listed below with a start date or end date within the "black out" period, then they will be presented with a notice (set by the administrator) stating the exceptional circumstances for that date (eg. 'Please note that our offices will only be open from 2:36 AM to 2:37 AM on this date in observance of Arbitrary Day.'). The adminsitrator can also set that no reservation can be created if its start or end date falls within the Black Out period.
<br>
 <%= link_to "Flash Message", {:url => flash_message_path},
                              :href => flash_message_path, :remote => true, :class => "btn", :id => "add_to_cart" %>

<br>
<table>
  <tr>
    <th>Equipment model</th>
    <th>Start date</th>
    <th>End date</th>
    <th>Notice</th>
    <th>Last Edited by</th>
    <th>Type</th>
    <th></th>
    <th></th>
    <th></th>
  </tr>

<% @black_outs.each do |black_out| %>
  <tr>
    <td><%= (black_out.equipment_model_id == 0) ? "All Equipment Models" : EquipmentModel.find(black_out.equipment_model_id).name %></td>
    <td><%= black_out[:start_date].strftime('%m/%d/%Y') %></td>
    <td><%= black_out[:end_date].strftime('%m/%d/%Y') %></td>
    <td><%= black_out.notice %></td>
    <td><%= User.find((black_out[:created_by])).name %></td>
    <td><%= black_out.black_out_type == 1 ? "Black Out" : "Notice Only" %></td>
    <td><%= link_to 'Show', black_out %></td>
    <td><%= link_to 'Edit', edit_black_out_path(black_out) %></td>
    <td><%= link_to 'Destroy', black_out, confirm: 'Are you sure?', method: :delete %></td>
  </tr>
<% end %>
</table>
<br />

